---
import LegalLayout from "@/components/layouts/LegalLayout.astro";
import LegalContact from "@/components/legal/LegalContact.astro";
import { createUrl } from "@/utils/url";
import { LEGAL_LAST_UPDATED } from "@/data/content";
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Cookie Policy"
  description="How AUXO Data Labs uses cookies, local storage, consent controls, and analytics-related technologies on auxodata.com."
  lastUpdated={LEGAL_LAST_UPDATED}
>
  <div class="legal-callout">
    <p>
      <strong>Current state.</strong> AUXO uses consent-aware analytics and
      browser storage for preferences. At the time of this update, we do
      <strong>not</strong> knowingly activate advertising cookies on the public
      site.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>1. What This Policy Covers</h2>
  <p>
    This Cookie Policy explains how Rapple International FZE, trading as AUXO
    Data Labs, uses cookies and similar technologies on
    <strong>auxodata.com</strong>.
  </p>
  <p>
    It should be read together with our
    <a href={createUrl("legal/privacy-policy")}>Privacy Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>2. What We Mean by Cookies and Similar Technologies</h2>
  <p>
    We use more than traditional browser cookies. Depending on the feature,
    data may be stored in a first-party cookie, in local storage, or handled
    through a consent-aware tag manager. In this policy, we refer to those
    together where that is the clearest explanation.
  </p>

  <h2>3. How Consent Works on This Site</h2>
  <p>
    AUXO uses Google Tag Manager with consent defaults that keep analytics and
    advertising storage denied until you make a choice. Essential functionality
    needed for security or core preferences can still operate.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Accept All:</strong> enables optional analytics and preference storage categories.</li>
    <li><strong>Reject All:</strong> keeps non-essential categories off.</li>
    <li><strong>Manage Preferences:</strong> lets you choose categories individually.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    You can reopen those controls through the
    <strong>Cookie Settings</strong> button in the footer.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Categories We Use</h2>
  <h3>4.1 Strictly Necessary</h3>
  <p>
    These support core site operation, consent state, and security-related
    behavior. Without them, parts of the experience may not work as expected.
  </p>

  <h3>4.2 Preferences</h3>
  <p>
    These remember choices such as your theme and can help restore an unfinished
    contact-form draft on the same device.
  </p>

  <h3>4.3 Analytics</h3>
  <p>
    These help us understand aggregate site usage and page engagement. They are
    optional and only intended to operate when you grant the relevant consent.
  </p>

  <h3>4.4 Marketing</h3>
  <p>
    We keep a marketing category in the consent interface for future expansion,
    but we do not knowingly activate marketing or advertising cookies on the
    public site as of <strong>April 3, 2026</strong>.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Current Cookie and Storage Declaration</h2>
  <table class="legal-table">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Identifier</th>
        <th>Provider</th>
        <th>Storage Type</th>
        <th>Purpose</th>
        <th>Typical Duration</th>
        <th>Category</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>auxo_consent_choice</code></td>
        <td>AUXO Data Labs</td>
        <td>Cookie</td>
        <td>Stores whether you have made a consent choice.</td>
        <td>Up to 12 months</td>
        <td>Strictly necessary</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>auxo_consent_*</code></td>
        <td>AUXO Data Labs</td>
        <td>Cookie</td>
        <td>Stores granted or denied states for analytics, marketing, and preference categories so GTM can apply consent before tags run.</td>
        <td>Up to 12 months</td>
        <td>Strictly necessary</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>theme</code></td>
        <td>AUXO Data Labs</td>
        <td>Local storage</td>
        <td>Remembers your light or dark theme preference.</td>
        <td>Persistent until changed or cleared</td>
        <td>Preferences</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>form_draft_contact-form</code></td>
        <td>AUXO Data Labs</td>
        <td>Local storage</td>
        <td>Temporarily stores an unfinished contact-form draft on your device.</td>
        <td>Up to 24 hours</td>
        <td>Preferences</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>_ga</code></td>
        <td>Google Analytics</td>
        <td>Cookie</td>
        <td>Distinguishes visitors for aggregate analytics reporting when analytics is enabled.</td>
        <td>Up to 2 years by default, subject to browser limits</td>
        <td>Analytics</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>_ga_*</code></td>
        <td>Google Analytics</td>
        <td>Cookie</td>
        <td>Persists session and measurement state for GA4 when analytics is enabled.</td>
        <td>Up to 2 years by default, subject to browser limits</td>
        <td>Analytics</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>
    <em>
      This table reflects the tools we can verify from the current site code.
      If we materially change cookie usage, we will update this page and the
      consent flow.
    </em>
  </p>

  <h2>6. Managing Cookies and Browser Storage</h2>
  <p>
    You can manage non-essential categories through our consent interface, and
    you can also clear cookies or local storage directly through your browser.
    Blocking storage entirely may affect features such as saved preferences or
    consent persistence.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Chrome</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://support.apple.com/guide/safari/manage-cookies-and-website-data-sfri11471/mac" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Safari</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/delete-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-63947406-40ac-c3b8-57b9-2a946a29ae09" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Microsoft Edge</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/enable-and-disable-cookies-website-preferences" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Mozilla Firefox</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>7. Third-Party Tools and Cross-Border Processing</h2>
  <p>
    Some site functions rely on third-party services such as Google Tag
    Manager, Google Analytics, or Google Calendar booking flows. Those services
    may process technical request data outside your country.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Updates to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may change this policy when the site, our tooling, or legal requirements
    change. The last-updated date at the top of the page shows the current
    version.
  </p>

  <LegalContact
    title="Cookie Questions"
    intro="For questions about consent choices, browser storage, or this Cookie Policy, contact:"
    email="privacy@auxodata.com"
  />
</LegalLayout>
